  "texts": [
    "Alzheimer's disease is a neurodegenerative condition that impairs brain function and destroys brain cells, altering memory and causing instability in human existence (Shankar and Walsh, 2009).",
    "Overproduction of amyloid-ß (Aß) and hyperphosphorylation of abnormal proteins are believed to be the two main contributors to AD pathogenesis.",
    "As a result, A-plaques and tau neurofibrillary entanglements accumulate and alter nucleocellular cytoplasmic transfer between neurons, leading to cell death and impaired memory and learning (Ramzan et al., 2020).",
    "The urgency of swift and precise disease identification and detection cannot be overstated.",
    "This is necessary because of economic expansion, the growth of information technology, and the advent of clinical information processing technologies."
  ],
